If you start to develop more in JavaScript you soon start to get the need for serving static files to your web browser while developing. Why a webserver? Because browsers often won't let you access remote data through ajax calls if you're operating from `file:///`.

Apache2 is a very nice and lightweight webserver environment which is setup in minutes on your machine.

